001.comments: If the course is full or blocked, please register in the waitlist section.CLST 331 is equivalent to ARTH 331. If this course is full, students can register in the equivalent section. ARTH 331 will apply towards Classical, Near Eastern and Religious Studies program requirements in the same way as CLST 331. Please contact the CNERS undergraduate advisor with any questions at cners.advising@ubc.ca.Students who have received credit for CLST 330 may not also receive credit for CLST 331 or 332.

WL1.comments: Waitlist for CLST 331-001. Note that ARTH 331 is the same course as CLST 331 and students may register in either section. Students will be manually moved in order of registration from the waitlist to the course section as seats become available. If the course is blocked but showing available seats, waitlist transfers have not yet taken place.

description: The visual culture of the ancient Greek world in the second and first millennia BCE, especially from c. 1000 to 30 BCE.
